PR #11631: HHH-18040 Support subqueries referencing the target table in MariaDB DML
Changed files (9): hibernate-community-dialects/src/main/java/org/hibernate/community/dialect/MariaDBLegacySqlAstTranslator.java, hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/dialect/sql/ast/MariaDBSqlAstTranslator.java, hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/sql/ast/spi/AbstractSqlAstTranslator.java, hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/sql/ast/spi/AggregateFunctionChecker.java, hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/sql/ast/spi/CorrelationChecker.java, hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/sql/ast/spi/NestedCorrelationChecker.java, hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/sql/ast/spi/NestedOrTargetTableCorrelationVisitor.java, hibernate-core/src/main/java/org/hibernate/sql/ast/tree/Statement.java, hibernate-core/src/test/java/org/hibernate/orm/test/hql/DmlSelfReferencingSubqueryTest.java
Diff (+355/-33):
PR DESCRIPTION:
The MySQL workaround for subqueries caused **correlation issues** in `MariaDB`, so I switched to **Single-table syntax** to resolve them.

